# Execution Log Capture

**Applies to every bot run** (paper_local, paper_live, live).

## Rules

1. During any bot execution session, monitor Docker logs throughout the run.
2. At the end of the run (teardown or stop), dump **all** container logs
   into `docs/execution_logs/`.
3. Name the log file with a timestamp in `YYYYMMDDHHmmss.log` format
   (e.g. `20260220021430.log`).
4. Capture logs from all services (trading-bot, monitor, analytics) into
   the single timestamped file, separated by service headers.
5. This folder is gitignored — logs stay local for analysis.
